    content: `Mickey Thompson is one of the most iconic names in American motorsport history. Marion Lee "Mickey" Thompson was a legendary racer, innovator, and entrepreneur who set numerous land speed records at the Bonneville Salt Flats in the 1950s and 1960s, including becoming the first American to exceed 400 mph. He went on to found Mickey Thompson Entertainment Group and develop tires and wheels specifically for performance and off-road applications. Today, Mickey Thompson Performance Tires and Wheels is part of the Cooper Tire family under Goodyear and continues to produce some of the most capable and recognizable off-road and performance tires on the market.

Mickey Thompson's approach to tire design reflects the no-compromise attitude of its founder. The brand invests heavily in developing proprietary technologies for extreme applications. Their PowerPly construction uses a three-ply polyester body with a nylon cap ply for enhanced strength and stability in large truck tires. SideBiter technology incorporates protective elements into the sidewall design to guard against cuts and abrasions during off-road use. These are not cosmetic features; they are functional engineering solutions born from real-world testing in the most demanding environments.

The Mickey Thompson lineup is focused on two areas: off-road truck tires and performance drag racing tires. In the off-road space, the Baja Boss series is their flagship, with the Baja Boss A/T providing an aggressive all-terrain option and the Baja Boss M/T delivering extreme mud-terrain capability with a design inspired by their Baja racing program. The Deegan 38 line, developed in collaboration with off-road racing champion Brian Deegan, offers a slightly more accessible range of all-terrain and mud-terrain options. On the performance side, Mickey Thompson's ET Street and Sportsman drag tires are staples at drag strips across the country.

Mickey Thompson tires are built for enthusiasts who push their vehicles to the limit. Off-road truck builders, Baja-style desert racers, drag strip competitors, and anyone who demands maximum capability from their tires will find Mickey Thompson to be a natural choice. The brand's racing heritage is not just a marketing story; it is an active, ongoing program that directly influences product development.

Ship.Tires carries Mickey Thompson because no off-road and performance tire inventory is complete without them. For drivers who demand the most capable tires available, Mickey Thompson delivers with authority. Explore our Mickey Thompson selection at ship.tires.`,
